# This an Express app setup using TypeScript

## Install dependencies

`npm install express
npm install --save-dev typescript @types/node @types/express ts-node
`

### express: The Express web framework.

### typescript: The TypeScript compiler.

### @types/node: Type definitions for Node.js.

### @types/express: Type definitions for Express.

### ts-node: A TypeScript execution engine for Node.js (helps with running TypeScript files directly).

## Create a tsconfig.json file

npx tsc --init

## Run the app

`npm run dev
npm run build
npm run start`

### start: Runs the compiled code from the dist/ directory.

### build: Compiles TypeScript code into JavaScript using tsc.

### dev: Runs the app directly with ts-node for development.
